<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}-{9}{y}={46}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{9}{y}={46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={46}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{46}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{{46}-{\left(-{9}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}\right)}+-{1}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{7}}\cdot{\left({46}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{7}}{\left(-{9}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{59.142857142857}-{\left(-{11.571428571429}\right)}{y}+-{1}{y}=-{34}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11.571428571429}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}=-{34}--{59.142857142857}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{11.571428571429}{y}+{\left(-{1}\right)}{y}={25.142857142857}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{11.571428571429}+{\left(-{1}\right)}\right)}{y}={25.142857142857}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12.571428571429}{y}={25.142857142857}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{25.142857142857}}{{-{{12.571428571429}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+-{9}{\left(-{2}\right)}={46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left({18}\right)}={46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={46}-{\left({18}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{28}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
